    "body": "Yep, I'm in favour of (4) so long as we limit the number of type parameters introduced on Beacon State to 1.\r\n\r\nI also think we should consider using `typenum`/`generic_array` to reduce the amount of boilerplate we have to write. My PoC for this is here, including boxing the array so it's stored on the heap: https://gist.github.com/michaelsproul/2c8e0d68617c736352ce9f4055cb295b\r\n\r\nThe only thing we lose by implementing (4) is the ability to load _arbitrary_ `ChainSpec`s at runtime and instantiate a `BeaconState` , although I don't think that is a great loss â€“ for our purposes a handful of parameter bundles should be sufficient (foundation, testing small, testing big, etc).",
